@startuml
!include _style.puml

title Metrics Flow

collections "Services\n(Entry-Hub, Security-Switch, Database-Vault,\nStorage-Service, Network-Manager, Certificate-Authority)" as Services <<service>>
participant "MQTT-Broker\n[Mosquitto]" as Broker <<infra>>
participant "Metrics-Collector" as Collector <<infra>>
database "TimescaleDB" as TSDB
participant "Grafana" as Grafana <<infra>>
actor "Admin" as Admin

note over Services
  Every service publishes, every minute and only, to its dedicated
  **metrics/<ServiceName>** topic via mTLS, after verifying the peer
  certificate comes from an MQTT-Broker and is a valid X.509 cert
  (EH-F-10, SS-F-07, DV-F-16, ST-F-12, NM-F-17, CA-F-03).
  Metrics carry aggregated statistics only: never personal data
  (EH-F-11, SS-F-08, DV-F-17, ST-F-13, NM-F-18).
end note

Services -> Broker : publish metrics/<ServiceName>
Broker -> Collector : subscribe metrics/* (MT-F-01)

alt "service" field matches source topic (MT-F-02, Mosquitto ACL)
  Collector -> TSDB : insert (hypertable)
else field mismatch
  Collector -> Collector : discard
end

note right of TSDB
  30-day retention,
  compression after 7 days (MT-F-03)
end note

Admin -> Grafana : open dashboards\n(response time, throughput,\nactive connections: MT-F-04)
Grafana -> TSDB : query raw / hourly-daily views,\nfiltered by service & metric name (UC-05)
TSDB --> Grafana : results
Grafana --> Admin : rendered dashboard

@enduml
